name Thai Asparagus Stew with Pineapple and Chilli Oil
serves 4
tags main, soup, thai, prawns, spring

- 750 g green asparagus
Peel the lower third, cut off the woody ends and halve diagonally lengthways.
-> asparagus

- 350 g pineapple
@nodep
Cut the pineapple into wedges.
-> pineapple

- 5 cloves garlic
- 1 tbsp peanut oil
@nodep
Peel the garlic, cut into thin slices and fry in {1} tbsp peanut oil until golden brown.
-> garlic

- 2 limes
@nodep
Finely zest {1} lime, then juice the limes to get {5} tbsp of juice.
-> lime zest and juice

- 30 g "fresh ginger"
@nodep
Peel and finely grate or purée the ginger.
-> ginger

- 800 g coconut milk
- 200 ml vegetable stock
- 1 tsp sugar
- salt
- "cayenne pepper"
@nodep
Simmer for 5 minutes over low heat. Season with salt, cayenne and sugar.
-> stew 1

= asparagus
@ stew 1
Add the asparagus and cook for 4-5 minutes.
-> stew 2

- 16 "prawns (cleaned, peeled)"
= pineapple
= ginger
= garlic
@ stew 2
Add the prawns, pineapple, ginger and garlic. Simmer for a further 3 minutes.
-> stew 3

- 2 tbsp peanut oil
- 3 tbsp dark sesame oil
- 1 tbsp Tabasco
- 5 "large basil leaves"
= lime zest and juice
@ stew 3
Finish with the peanut oil, sesame oil, Tabasco, basil and lime.
